Description: WiFi wardriving application for GNOME
 GNOME Wardrive is a WiFi wardriving application that allows users to scan
 for wireless networks and collect information about them. It provides a
 modern GTK4/Libadwaita interface for monitoring WiFi networks, collecting
 GPS coordinates, and exporting data for analysis.
 .
 Features include:
  - Real-time WiFi network scanning
  - GPS coordinate collection via GeoClue
  - Export data to various formats
  - Modern GNOME interface
  - Mobile-friendly responsive design